(42, 22, 70, 42, 23, 3, 3, 'Art thou then the Son of God?', 'Connection of Identity Claims', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' identity through direct questions about his nature. In each instance, he responds affirmatively, indicating a recognition of his role as the Son of God and King of the Jews.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
